<p>The language stuff is interesting too: Geld to guilt. The German word for guilt, Schuld, is also their word for debt and obligation. Relating to that is Schulter, which is shoulder, which can be used in English as a verb for carrying a load or burden, e.g. to shoulder the blame. Fascinating (in my opinion).</p>
