<p>Mr Graeber thinks corporations are part of the problem but I disagree. Corporations are part of the solution ONCE they no longer have the government backed counterfeiting cartel, the banking system, to borrow from. Then it is very likely that corporations will be forced by competitive pressure to &#8220;share&#8221; wealth (use their common stock as money) rather than reap it.</p>
<p>Almost all our problems can be traced backed to government backed usury and counterfeiting. Abolish that and we will have eliminated the &#8220;root of all sorts of evil&#8221; (1 Timothy 6:10).</p>
