<section class="comment-content comment">
<p>And to relate that back to the &#8220;internal control&#8221; problem (and it is the problem), productive employees and the knowledge workers responsible for innovation do not benefit from looting. </p>
<p>Leaving the real talent stuck in a structure that cloaks management&#8217;s activities in secrecy is only good for management&#8217;s chosen activities of looting and politicking, not for &#8220;innovation&#8221; of any other sort.</p>
</section>
