<article id="comment-452426" class="comment">
<header class="comment-meta comment-author vcard">
<cite><b class="fn"><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20230122074248/https://thingumbobesquire.blogspot.com/" rel="external nofollow ugc" class="url">Thingumbob</a></b> </cite><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20230122074248/https://www.nakedcapitalism.com/2011/08/what-is-debt-%e2%80%93-an-interview-with-economic-anthropologist-david-graeber.html#comment-452426"><time datetime="2011-08-26T10:10:29-04:00">August 26, 2011 at 10:10 am</time></a> </header>
<section class="comment-content comment">
<p>While much of Mr Graeber&#8217;s work is unobjectionable and his criticism of the IMF, et al. is appreciated, the problem is that the entire field of academic &#8220;economics&#8221; itself is a fraud. It entirely leaves out of the question that there is a physical economy apart from money. And, it just so happens that that study of the improvements in that physical economy and how populations are sustained at increasing standards of living is the only way out of the current monetary crisis. Yes, debt moratoria are required, but then the question is what sorts of long term investments are necessary to pull the world away from the last 50 years of looting the world&#8217;s physical economy?</p>
</section>
<div class="reply">
</div>
</article>
