<li class="comment odd alt depth-5" id="li-comment-453357">
<article id="comment-453357" class="comment">
<header class="comment-meta comment-author vcard">
<cite><b class="fn">MyLessThanPrimeBeef</b> </cite><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20230122074248/https://www.nakedcapitalism.com/2011/08/what-is-debt-%e2%80%93-an-interview-with-economic-anthropologist-david-graeber.html#comment-453357"><time datetime="2011-08-27T13:06:18-04:00">August 27, 2011 at 1:06 pm</time></a> </header>
<section class="comment-content comment">
<p>Reader, I&#8217;m trying to figure out which came first &#8211; bartering or borrowing, bith among tribal members and with outsiders. Money, here or from outerspace, or writing is assumed to have happened after one of those two.</p>
</section>
<div class="reply">
