<p>&#8220;The final outcome was in many ways profoundly libratory for the bulk of those who lived through it – chattel slavery, for example, was largely eliminated from the great civilizations.&#8221;</p>
<p>libratory, from libration &#8211; A very slow oscillation, real or apparent, of a satellite as viewed from the larger celestial body around which it revolves (libra-scale).</p>
<p>Although your essay has a world-historical sweep, from the context I think you meant:</p>
<p>liberatory &#8211; tending, or serving, to liberate. </p>
<p>Or was it a typo Phillip? </p>
