<p>To make up for it, perhaps a second suggestion: Have you read/are you familiar with David Harvey&#8217;s <i>Cosmopolitanism and the Geographies of Freedom</i>? I found it a most intriguing (and very well-written) work. Among many other things, the book teaches the reader to recognize the spurious conflation of the absolute conception of space with the political-geographical conception of the world separated into states.</p>
