<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-453443">
<article id="comment-453443" class="comment">
<header class="comment-meta comment-author vcard">
<cite><b class="fn">Alex</b> </cite><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20230122074248/https://www.nakedcapitalism.com/2011/08/what-is-debt-%e2%80%93-an-interview-with-economic-anthropologist-david-graeber.html#comment-453443"><time datetime="2011-08-27T14:46:38-04:00">August 27, 2011 at 2:46 pm</time></a> </header>
<section class="comment-content comment">
<p>I was so impressed by this interview, I went looking for other stuff by the same guy. <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20230122074248/http://www.charlierose.com/view/interview/473" rel="nofollow">This interview</a> with Charlie Rose, from 2006, just after he&#8217;d been fired by Yale, is very, very good. I will definitely be reading this book.</p>
</section>
