<p>Dr. Graeber,</p>
<p>I am very late to this conversation but I am quite curious&#8230;.</p>
<p>You state in the post, &#8220;In Sanskrit, Hebrew, Aramaic, ‘debt,’ ‘guilt,’ and ‘sin’ are actually the same word.&#8221; I cannot think of a word in Hebrew or Aramaic that has the same root for all three concepts, but I know that, at least as far as &#8220;sin&#8221; is concerned, both languages have a rich vocabulary :-) Could you let me know which root word you were thinking of when you wrote that?</p>
</section>
<div class="reply">
