<ol class="children">
<li class="comment odd alt depth-2" id="li-comment-456774">
<article id="comment-456774" class="comment">
<header class="comment-meta comment-author vcard">
<cite><b class="fn">David Graeber</b> </cite><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20230122074248/https://www.nakedcapitalism.com/2011/08/what-is-debt-%e2%80%93-an-interview-with-economic-anthropologist-david-graeber.html#comment-456774"><time datetime="2011-08-31T23:22:06-04:00">August 31, 2011 at 11:22 pm</time></a> </header>
<section class="comment-content comment">
<p>Actually I would agree &#8211; we know that democratically organized autonomous city states existed in the late Iron Age, and not just in Greece but India, and elsewhere, but we don&#8217;t really have anthropological evidence of those in later periods. </p>
<p>However, there is an incredibly wide variety of cases from anthropology &#8211; there are literally thousands of different sorts of money that have been documented put to an incredibly wide variety of usages. There are an endless variety of system of exchange. If despite this you find everything _but_ the hypothetical imaginary explanation you came up with in your armchair, then saying &#8220;so what, I bet in precisely the period we don&#8217;t know about, they did exactly that&#8221; &#8211; I call that special pleading.</p>
</section>
<div class="reply">
