<section class="comment-content comment">
<p>This is really interesting. Reminds me of a class I took with Richard Wilk.</p>
<p>If I could ask Professor Graeber another question, it would have been: How did &#8220;shocks&#8221; permeate through the system?</p>
<p>Say one of my cows is eaten so I can&#8217;t &#8220;sell&#8221; as much milk &#8212; would I still be able to get food, oil, &amp;c? Or say my crops do really well &#8212; do I have to give it away at the same &#8220;price&#8221;? What is the &#8220;elasticity of demand&#8221; if you get my drift.</p>
</section>
